external_knowledge:
- 'Challenging' trails refer to those with a difficulty level of 'hard';
- 'A full morning' is considered to be approximately 10 hours or more of hiking time;
- 'Highly rated' trails have a rating over 4 stars (out of 5).

- 'Hard' difficulty indicates the most challenging trails suitable only for experienced hikers;
- Distance > 1000 kilometers refers to extremely long trails that are rare and demanding;
- The 'priority' in the context of categories suggests the order of importance or recommendation for hikers.

sql:
SELECT user_id, username, email
FROM users
WHERE user_id IN (SELECT user_id FROM hikes);

SELECT trail_id, average_rating
FROM trail_statistics
WHERE hike_count > 3;

external_knowledge:
- "winding paths of our hiking odyssey" refers to the hiking trails;
- "names and lengths of the routes" refer to the route names and distances of trails;
- "tales of their steepness" refers to the difficulty of the trails, while "whispers of their trail conditions" and "murmur of their scenic beauty" pertain to the breakdown of user ratings for trail condition and scenery, respectively;
- "voyagers who shared their stories" refers to the reviewers of the trails.

sql:
SELECT AVG(ts.total_photos) AS average_photos
FROM trail_statistics ts
WHERE ts.average_rating > 4.5 AND ts.hike_count > 5;
